WEBVTT

00:07.616 --> 00:09.376
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

00:37.833 --> 00:41.153
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

00:41.153 --> 00:43.040
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

00:57.400 --> 01:00.567
Why did you ask to see me?

01:00.567 --> 01:04.267
You've been featured on every TV program

01:04.267 --> 01:06.600
covering the Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

01:07.233 --> 01:09.233
You were involved
in the investigation too, right?

01:10.200 --> 01:14.533
I thought you might know
whether I'm the real killer or not.

01:15.200 --> 01:17.402
My opinion doesn't matter.

01:18.033 --> 01:21.133
Your DNA has already been identified,
Mr. Lee Yong Woo.

01:25.867 --> 01:27.467
I'm not sure about that...

01:30.067 --> 01:33.500
Why do you keep denying the crimes?

01:33.500 --> 01:36.200
The statute of limitations
has already expired,

01:36.200 --> 01:40.000
and you won't be punished for this anyway.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.200
Then why are the police digging up a case

01:43.200 --> 01:46.567
beyond the statute of limitations?

01:46.567 --> 01:49.233
You won't be able to convict me anyway.

01:50.700 --> 01:53.184
This isn't about convicting you.

01:55.067 --> 01:57.933
We just want to uncover the truth.

02:00.867 --> 02:02.767
Nine innocent victims,

02:02.767 --> 02:06.233
and their families
who were forced to let them go.

02:08.267 --> 02:09.867
On top of that,

02:11.700 --> 02:14.100
everyone who lived in Kangseng

02:14.867 --> 02:17.267
back then

02:17.900 --> 02:20.367
has the right to know the truth.

02:22.467 --> 02:25.567
Because it changed so much of their lives.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.640
Well,

02:28.640 --> 02:30.433
that makes sense.

02:38.400 --> 02:41.900
[Confession is the beginning of forgiveness,
and forgiveness opens the door to salvation]

02:41.900 --> 02:44.100
But still, it wasn't me.

02:45.633 --> 02:47.433
I didn't do it.

02:59.967 --> 03:01.767
All right then.

03:12.533 --> 03:14.300
Are you leaving already?

03:16.600 --> 03:18.500
I'll come again tomorrow.

03:33.400 --> 03:35.633
Stay out of my sight as much as possible.

03:35.633 --> 03:37.733
It won't take long!

03:37.733 --> 03:40.100
[Episode 2]
I don't plan on staying here long anyway.

03:42.633 --> 03:44.400
Kang Tae Joo!

03:49.200 --> 03:51.767
I'll take this case back.

03:54.933 --> 03:56.633
And you too.

03:57.533 --> 03:58.700
What?

03:58.700 --> 04:00.160
I will

04:00.160 --> 04:02.533
keep you by my side.

04:02.533 --> 04:04.233
Like back then.

04:06.933 --> 04:09.000
You psycho!

04:09.000 --> 04:12.367
I missed you, Kang Tae Joo.

04:23.233 --> 04:25.200
- You're splashing.
- Darn it.

04:26.433 --> 04:30.600
Tae Joo!

04:31.433 --> 04:35.133
Dead or alive?

04:35.133 --> 04:37.433
Alive!

04:37.433 --> 04:40.067
This is really not fun.

04:40.067 --> 04:41.967
Tae Joo!

04:41.967 --> 04:44.100
It's a joke, just a joke.

04:49.536 --> 04:51.100
- You punk!
- Hey, hey!

04:51.100 --> 04:53.300
Hold on, hold on!

05:01.267 --> 05:03.967
Were you scared? Afraid you got shot?

05:03.967 --> 05:05.033
You punk!

05:05.033 --> 05:06.433
How dare you try to shoot a prosecutor?

05:06.433 --> 05:08.367
Didn't you say we were friends?

05:08.367 --> 05:10.500
Since we are friends...

05:11.200 --> 05:13.200
why not...

05:13.200 --> 05:15.500
It's a joke, just a joke.

05:15.500 --> 05:17.533
A joke?

05:17.533 --> 05:19.264
Well?

05:19.264 --> 05:21.433
Not fun to you?

05:21.433 --> 05:23.067
It wasn't fun to me, either.

05:25.033 --> 05:28.067
Back then, your little jokes
weren't fun at all, either.

05:32.800 --> 05:35.296
[Period for Reporting and Surrendering Spies]

05:39.867 --> 05:42.867
I'll take this case back.

05:42.867 --> 05:44.500
And you too.

06:08.600 --> 06:10.200
Lee Seong Jin.

06:10.200 --> 06:11.744
I got

06:11.744 --> 06:13.433
released today.

06:14.133 --> 06:17.567
It's all thanks to you, Detective.

06:18.842 --> 06:21.633
[Kangseng Police Station]

06:21.633 --> 06:23.233
You've been through a lot.

06:25.500 --> 06:27.467
Live a proper life from now on.

06:28.267 --> 06:30.600
For your mother's sake, at least.

06:30.600 --> 06:32.233
Yes, sir.

06:32.933 --> 06:34.567
I'm really glad

06:36.067 --> 06:39.233
that you came back to Kangseng, Detective.

06:39.233 --> 06:41.792
I really wanted

06:41.792 --> 06:44.067
to tell you this.

06:46.656 --> 06:48.800
Bye.

06:54.900 --> 06:56.544
Well...

06:57.600 --> 06:58.867
Glad?

07:09.667 --> 07:14.100
It has now been confirmed that
the series of murders since October 1986

07:14.100 --> 07:17.152
are connected as a serial killing case.

07:17.152 --> 07:18.300
Yes?

07:18.300 --> 07:21.933
So how many cases are there in total?

07:21.933 --> 07:25.700
As far as we've confirmed so far,
there are four cases in total.

07:27.808 --> 07:31.433
- Go ahead.
- Why is this only being revealed now?

07:31.433 --> 07:34.800
Because the culprit's methods
changed slightly over time,

07:34.800 --> 07:37.900
it took time before we could
make an official announcement,

07:37.900 --> 07:41.167
but a joint police-prosecution task force
has already been formed.

07:41.167 --> 07:44.333
We are doing all we can
to apprehend the culprit.

07:46.000 --> 07:48.133
What do you mean the method changed?

07:48.133 --> 07:49.567
Mr. Hwang is so busy lately.

07:49.567 --> 07:50.700
I can barely see him.

07:50.700 --> 07:52.300
It's killing me too.

07:52.300 --> 07:55.833
All his other cases have been dumped on me.

07:55.833 --> 07:57.933
Handling the student protest cases alone
is enough of a headache.

07:57.933 --> 07:59.467
Why are you handling everything?

07:59.467 --> 08:01.167
What about Mr. Cha?

08:03.267 --> 08:04.500
Hand some of them over to me.

08:04.500 --> 08:06.633
No way. How could I possibly...

08:06.633 --> 08:08.667
It's okay. I've got plenty
of free time these days.

08:08.667 --> 08:10.700
This is exactly when
we should help each other out.

08:10.700 --> 08:12.733
Then, should I

08:12.733 --> 08:15.967
- take the protest case at least?
- Yeah, let him take it.

08:17.667 --> 08:20.067
I'd appreciate that if you would.

08:20.067 --> 08:21.667
Alright, then.

08:22.533 --> 08:23.967
It's been a long time.

08:23.967 --> 08:25.900
Make sure you get a good close shot.

08:25.900 --> 08:27.067
Stay for a meal.

08:27.067 --> 08:28.133
Reporters,

08:28.133 --> 08:30.767
lunch will be served at Seoul Hall
in the town center.

08:30.767 --> 08:32.200
- Okay.
- Thank you.

08:32.200 --> 08:33.833
Okay.

08:40.400 --> 08:42.000
I'm about to

08:42.000 --> 08:44.967
lay out a really great spread.

08:44.967 --> 08:47.367
But I don't like the guy holding the spoon.

08:47.367 --> 08:48.967
It takes all the fun out of it.

08:48.967 --> 08:51.667
Then give it to someone else.

08:54.500 --> 08:56.967
I might have to grab a spoon myself then.

08:56.967 --> 08:59.000
Well, are you hungry?

08:59.000 --> 09:00.933
No. I'm already full,

09:00.933 --> 09:03.300
thinking about the scoop I'm about to land.

09:03.300 --> 09:05.433
We're having a scoop?

09:05.433 --> 09:07.500
Clean your lens properly.

09:07.500 --> 09:10.600
You'll be photographing
the arrest of a serial killer.

09:10.600 --> 09:14.100
How would we know when or where
the suspect gets caught?

09:14.100 --> 09:16.267
I know who will catch him.

09:20.433 --> 09:22.267
Sir.

09:22.267 --> 09:23.300
I watched your press conference.

09:23.300 --> 09:25.400
Mr. Cha.

09:28.767 --> 09:33.167
Why did you choose me over Mr. Cha?

09:33.167 --> 09:37.533
I'm curious why you took the longer path
instead of the easy one.

09:38.633 --> 09:40.933
I'm pretty good at reading faces.

09:42.067 --> 09:44.467
Do I have a good one?

09:44.467 --> 09:46.048
More like

09:46.048 --> 09:49.367
that prosecutor over there
just doesn't look promising.

09:53.400 --> 09:56.067
Why? Is there something on my face?

09:56.067 --> 09:58.867
Huh? No, nothing.

09:58.867 --> 10:01.500
So, do you have something to say to me?

10:01.500 --> 10:04.367
Would you please make some time this evening?

10:04.367 --> 10:05.567
I have something to discuss with you.

10:05.567 --> 10:07.333
Ah, I'm not sure.

10:07.333 --> 10:10.467
My son's home for vacation.

10:10.467 --> 10:12.267
Cheol?

10:12.267 --> 10:15.767
Wow, he's already in college.

10:15.767 --> 10:17.167
Time flies!

10:17.167 --> 10:19.767
- It sure does.
- Bring him to the office sometime.

10:19.767 --> 10:21.167
I'd like to meet him.

10:21.167 --> 10:22.533
Yeah, maybe.

10:22.533 --> 10:25.000
Anyway, let's have that meal another time.

10:29.967 --> 10:32.233
"Mom is cooking," done writing?

10:32.233 --> 10:34.000
Yes!

10:34.000 --> 10:37.733
Number 3, "I played with my friend."

10:41.567 --> 10:44.267
"I played with my friend.'"

10:52.700 --> 10:53.733
Good job today.

10:53.733 --> 10:55.233
[Nurturing dreams with learning and love]
Alright, take care on your way.

10:55.233 --> 10:57.067
- I'll get going.
- Bye.

10:57.067 --> 10:58.700
Guys!

11:01.067 --> 11:03.033
- Hello.
- Hello.

11:23.433 --> 11:24.933
You almost got me there.

11:24.933 --> 11:26.500
Oh, that was so close.

11:26.500 --> 11:29.033
I thought I'd actually hit you this time.

11:29.033 --> 11:30.667
Have you eaten?

11:33.344 --> 11:34.933
Let's go grab something to eat.

11:36.367 --> 11:38.233
- I'm hungry.
- You're hungry?

11:38.233 --> 11:40.400
Yeah, with that growling.

11:41.867 --> 11:43.867
They say Tae Joo came back here.

11:44.767 --> 11:47.767
He came home completely wasted.

11:47.767 --> 11:50.033
Life was peaceful while he was away.

11:50.033 --> 11:53.000
Now to think about living
with him again is annoying.

11:54.033 --> 11:55.900
Then,

11:55.900 --> 11:57.500
want to live with me?

11:59.333 --> 12:01.167
Let's get married.

12:03.467 --> 12:07.067
Why are you proposing
in a rice soup restaurant?

12:07.067 --> 12:08.768
Don't say yes.

12:08.768 --> 12:10.900
It's not like that.

12:16.533 --> 12:18.500
Why aren't you answering?

12:20.800 --> 12:22.933
Don't you want to marry me?

12:22.933 --> 12:24.567
I'm not sure.

12:39.867 --> 12:43.067
Ma'am, I said no intestines.

12:43.067 --> 12:44.867
Oh dear, I forgot.

12:44.867 --> 12:48.100
What to do?
I can't swap it now that it's served.

12:48.100 --> 12:49.300
I'll just eat it.

12:49.300 --> 12:51.033
Sorry.

12:53.033 --> 12:54.667
Wait.

12:58.367 --> 13:00.833
I'm not asking you to decide right now.

13:04.667 --> 13:07.133
Think about it carefully.

13:08.300 --> 13:09.900
Wait a moment.

13:11.733 --> 13:13.500
There.

13:14.667 --> 13:16.267
Here.

13:17.700 --> 13:18.733
Go on, have some.

13:18.733 --> 13:20.333
You have some too.

13:30.900 --> 13:34.067
Why are you moping alone?

13:35.033 --> 13:36.633
Is something wrong?

13:37.533 --> 13:39.133
Sang Beom.

13:40.267 --> 13:41.700
Tae Joo is back.

13:41.700 --> 13:43.367
Kang Tae Joo?

13:44.700 --> 13:46.800
Wait, that punk is here?

13:53.133 --> 13:56.033
Darn it.

13:56.033 --> 13:59.433
He's not going to start cracking down
around here again, is he?

13:59.433 --> 14:02.300
You little punk, you scared?

14:02.300 --> 14:06.133
Well, it's not that I'm scared,
but he's a bit...

14:06.133 --> 14:09.833
Anyway, be careful.
He's not someone to mess with.

14:09.833 --> 14:12.233
Back then at least we knew his weakness.

14:12.233 --> 14:15.467
If it's a weakness, we can find another one.

14:15.467 --> 14:17.367
That's right.

14:19.400 --> 14:21.567
[Kangseng Police Station]

14:21.567 --> 14:23.133
Let's start by finding the victims.

14:23.133 --> 14:26.467
But are there any surviving victims?
There aren't any.

14:26.467 --> 14:29.467
No, there haven't been
any attempted murder cases yet.

14:29.467 --> 14:32.867
- Exactly.
- He abducts, rapes, and then kills.

14:32.867 --> 14:35.000
What if things went wrong
before it went all the way?

14:35.000 --> 14:37.433
Attempted kidnapping, or attempted rape?

14:37.433 --> 14:38.733
Or rape.

14:38.733 --> 14:40.567
There's no way there'd be anything like that.

14:40.567 --> 14:42.267
That punk is human too.

14:42.267 --> 14:44.700
You think he never makes mistakes?

14:46.300 --> 14:49.567
Alright, start by looking for any sex crimes
in Kangseng over the past two years

14:49.567 --> 14:52.633
that bear even the slightest
resemblance to this case.

14:52.633 --> 14:55.233
Any unusual details?

14:55.233 --> 14:58.133
- When meeting victims of sexual crimes,
- I don't know.

14:58.133 --> 15:00.333
make sure to bring along a female officer.

15:04.300 --> 15:05.900
Thank you.

15:08.367 --> 15:10.267
Where are we going next?

15:11.233 --> 15:14.200
The end of...

15:14.200 --> 15:16.400
this alley.

15:16.400 --> 15:18.367
Okay, let's go.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.433
There must be a witness
among them who saw him.

15:38.467 --> 15:40.667
- Thank you.
- Eat a lot.

15:40.667 --> 15:42.000
Oh my, Mom.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.300
Looks like you really
like your second daughter-in-law.

15:44.300 --> 15:45.633
I know, right?

15:45.633 --> 15:48.533
Mother, you're making me feel left out.

15:48.533 --> 15:51.200
There's nothing to feel left out about.

15:51.200 --> 15:54.816
Oh dear, you should hurry
and have a baby first.

15:54.816 --> 15:56.800
Mom.

15:56.800 --> 15:57.967
Why talk about babies?

15:57.967 --> 16:00.300
Even Ki Hwan doesn't have one yet.

16:00.300 --> 16:03.433
Have a smart kid
who takes after you instead of him.

16:03.433 --> 16:04.633
That way you won't suffer.

16:04.633 --> 16:08.833
This one's all grown physically
but still just a kid.

16:08.833 --> 16:12.467
Mom, you said I was your favorite, remember?

16:12.467 --> 16:16.167
Ki Beom, did you properly
introduce yourself to Tae Joo?

16:16.900 --> 16:18.567
Not yet.

16:19.567 --> 16:23.767
Why? Does Tae Joo not like him?

16:23.767 --> 16:26.433
No, it's just that
he hasn't hardly been home lately.

16:26.433 --> 16:30.267
Well, with that serial killer case,
he must be swamped.

16:30.267 --> 16:31.833
Yeah.

16:31.833 --> 16:35.167
What kind of bad omen is this
with a wedding coming up?

16:35.167 --> 16:39.533
The bride's family should set the date.

16:39.533 --> 16:41.967
Go introduce yourself properly first.

16:41.967 --> 16:43.033
Got it?

16:43.033 --> 16:44.633
Got it.

16:51.386 --> 16:53.067
Well...

16:53.067 --> 16:55.067
What if Tae Joo doesn't like me?

16:55.067 --> 16:56.400
Doesn't like you?

16:56.400 --> 16:58.167
No way.

16:58.167 --> 17:01.700
He might care about me as his friend's
brother, but maybe not as his brother-in-law.

17:01.700 --> 17:04.333
I don't even have a decent job.

17:05.167 --> 17:06.912
Honestly,

17:06.912 --> 17:09.567
you are too good for me.

17:09.567 --> 17:11.533
I'm the one who hit the jackpot.

17:13.967 --> 17:15.600
Lee Ki Beom.

17:16.300 --> 17:18.633
How many teachers do you think
there are in Kangseng?

17:19.500 --> 17:21.280
I don't know.

17:21.280 --> 17:22.304
About a hundred?

17:22.304 --> 17:24.500
Teachers are common.

17:24.500 --> 17:27.100
Then in Kangseng,

17:27.100 --> 17:30.100
how many men are as handsome as Andy Lau?

17:33.000 --> 17:34.733
Just you.

17:34.733 --> 17:38.333
I'm the one who hit the jackpot, got it?

17:40.900 --> 17:42.367
Comparing me to Andy Lau is a bit much.

17:42.367 --> 17:45.400
Why? I think you're way more handsome.

17:45.400 --> 17:47.200
- Really?
- Yes!

17:49.466 --> 17:50.720
[Kangseng Police Station]
Hey.

17:52.867 --> 17:54.733
Your socks and underwear.

17:54.733 --> 17:57.467
You should've brought more.

17:57.467 --> 17:59.433
How long are you gonna be away?

17:59.433 --> 18:01.500
Go home now.

18:01.500 --> 18:04.067
What kind of clothes are these?

18:04.067 --> 18:08.633
Don't walk alone at night.
I'll tell Ki Beom to walk you home.

18:08.633 --> 18:10.467
Already did.

18:10.467 --> 18:13.600
Really? That's sweet of him.

18:13.600 --> 18:15.267
Since when?

18:15.267 --> 18:17.833
Maybe about three years?

18:19.300 --> 18:20.533
Are you two dating?

18:20.533 --> 18:22.333
We're getting married.

18:24.992 --> 18:28.467
You'll come to my wedding, right?

18:28.467 --> 18:29.900
When is it?

18:29.900 --> 18:32.867
You pick the date. Whatever works for you.

18:32.867 --> 18:34.500
- Wait...
- Gotta go.

18:39.967 --> 18:41.267
- Hello.
- Oh.

18:41.267 --> 18:42.900
Hello, how are you?

18:42.900 --> 18:45.233
What's going on?

18:45.233 --> 18:46.912
She told me

18:46.912 --> 18:48.467
to set the date.

18:48.467 --> 18:49.800
The date for what?

18:49.800 --> 18:51.367
My little sister's wedding day.

18:51.367 --> 18:53.333
- She's getting married?
- Seems so.

18:53.333 --> 18:55.200
That's great news, congrats. And?

18:55.200 --> 18:58.867
Well, I've only ever caught criminals,
but I've never set a wedding date.

18:59.867 --> 19:03.367
Isn't it kind of similar
to catching a criminal?

19:03.367 --> 19:04.567
Really?

19:04.567 --> 19:07.167
What are you idiots even talking about?

19:07.167 --> 19:09.533
Do you want to mess up
such an important family event?

19:09.533 --> 19:11.233
- For a special day like that,
- Yeah.

19:11.233 --> 19:13.600
you go to a good fortune-teller

19:13.600 --> 19:17.100
and set an auspicious date.

19:17.100 --> 19:19.200
Pay them well.

19:21.967 --> 19:24.333
Well... Detective Kang.

19:24.333 --> 19:26.500
I have something to tell you.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.367
Alright.

19:29.367 --> 19:31.936
About a month ago,

19:31.936 --> 19:33.067
on her way home,

19:33.067 --> 19:36.233
she said she was abducted by a man.

19:37.000 --> 19:39.967
With her hands tied behind her back.

19:48.433 --> 19:52.667
Please help me!

19:52.667 --> 19:56.800
Please help me!

19:59.433 --> 20:01.824
Please save me...

20:01.824 --> 20:03.500
- Oh my.
- Oh, no. Are you alright?

20:03.500 --> 20:04.800
Honey, call the police!

20:04.800 --> 20:05.900
Call the police?

20:05.900 --> 20:09.067
Miss, can you stand up?

20:10.488 --> 20:12.192
[Police]

20:12.833 --> 20:15.567
I don't want to report it.

20:15.567 --> 20:17.633
What? Why not?

20:17.633 --> 20:20.500
I'm too scared to do it.

20:20.500 --> 20:25.967
She refused firmly,
so we just escorted her home.

20:25.967 --> 20:29.033
So that's why there's no record.

20:29.033 --> 20:31.767
Her hands were tied behind her back

20:31.767 --> 20:33.867
with a handkerchief too.

21:03.467 --> 21:06.067
I'm sure I told you

21:06.067 --> 21:08.133
that I didn't want to report it.

21:08.133 --> 21:09.200
Well, about that...

21:09.200 --> 21:11.833
Nothing actually happened.

21:11.833 --> 21:13.233
Really.

21:13.233 --> 21:15.733
- But you said you were abducted.
- That's...

21:18.033 --> 21:20.267
But I didn't die.

21:20.267 --> 21:22.867
And nothing terrible happened.

21:24.800 --> 21:26.767
You were lucky.

21:32.233 --> 21:36.000
What kind of 'lucky' woman
goes through something like that?

21:36.000 --> 21:40.433
I can't even be alone at night
because of what happened that day.

21:40.433 --> 21:43.967
If a stranger talks to me,
my whole body freezes.

21:43.967 --> 21:46.300
I can't live normally anymore.

21:47.067 --> 21:49.200
And you call that 'lucky'?

21:49.200 --> 21:51.100
After all, the other victims

21:52.767 --> 21:54.967
didn't survive.

21:56.867 --> 21:58.833
But you did, Ms. Park Ae Sook.

22:00.416 --> 22:02.208
My goodness.

22:08.300 --> 22:09.933
That day,

22:10.633 --> 22:14.133
I was on my way back from a blind date.

22:17.000 --> 22:19.767
We were supposed to have some tea,

22:19.767 --> 22:22.733
but it turned into dinner and went long.

22:28.233 --> 22:31.200
He was a nice guy.

22:31.200 --> 22:34.633
I thought luck was finally
on my side that day.

22:36.633 --> 22:38.336
Did you

22:38.336 --> 22:41.400
happen to see something like a scarecrow?

22:44.100 --> 22:46.367
I think I did.

23:02.833 --> 23:04.533
Where are your stockings?

23:06.592 --> 23:08.224
I...

23:08.224 --> 23:09.472
Darn it.

23:09.472 --> 23:10.567
Yes...

23:10.567 --> 23:12.900
Yes, I have stockings.

23:12.900 --> 23:16.500
I took them off because they were torn.

23:16.500 --> 23:18.767
They're in my purse, I swear.

23:18.767 --> 23:19.800
Your purse?

23:19.800 --> 23:22.300
I dropped it over there earlier.

23:26.467 --> 23:27.533
Stay here.

23:27.533 --> 23:29.233
Okay.

23:39.800 --> 23:41.767
I just knew

23:41.767 --> 23:45.133
if I didn't run then, I would die.

23:50.667 --> 23:52.833
I was so scared.

23:52.833 --> 23:56.233
Afraid that man would come back any moment.

23:56.233 --> 23:59.100
Oh dear, what on earth happened?

23:59.100 --> 24:00.133
Are you alright?

24:00.133 --> 24:02.900
Honey, call the police!

24:02.900 --> 24:04.900
Miss, can you stand up?

24:13.733 --> 24:16.467
Did you see the suspect's face?

24:17.667 --> 24:20.000
I avoided eye contact.

24:20.000 --> 24:21.933
I thought he'd kill me if I didn't.

24:23.967 --> 24:26.000
I know this is hard,

24:26.000 --> 24:28.352
but is there anything else?

24:28.352 --> 24:30.067
Anything you remember helps.

24:32.500 --> 24:35.400
He was thin.

24:35.400 --> 24:37.733
Average height?

24:38.400 --> 24:40.733
Just ordinary.

24:42.700 --> 24:46.900
Did you not report it
because you feared retaliation?

24:50.000 --> 24:52.433
My purse was gone.

24:53.767 --> 24:55.600
The suspect probably took it, right?

24:55.600 --> 24:58.633
My ID was in there.

24:58.633 --> 25:02.033
That means he's got my name and address.

25:03.200 --> 25:04.704
So

25:04.704 --> 25:06.933
how could I report it?

25:19.633 --> 25:22.267
Like you said, Ms. Park,

25:22.267 --> 25:25.333
maybe you weren't lucky after all.

25:26.200 --> 25:30.000
You went through something
you shouldn't have, like the other victims.

25:30.000 --> 25:33.067
But what saved you then

25:33.067 --> 25:35.767
wasn't luck, but yourself.

25:39.233 --> 25:41.400
Your courage, Ms. Park.

25:52.233 --> 25:55.800
When we catch him,
you'll be the first to know.

25:55.800 --> 25:57.733
One more thing,

25:57.733 --> 26:00.967
I'm not sure if this helps,

26:01.900 --> 26:04.567
but that man's hand...

26:05.633 --> 26:10.167
It felt soft... like a woman's hand.

26:19.967 --> 26:23.000
[Kangseng Bookstore]

26:33.033 --> 26:34.833
Hello.

26:35.600 --> 26:37.400
I'm here

26:37.400 --> 26:41.067
to pick up a reference book,

26:43.133 --> 26:45.167
under Yu Jeong Rin.

26:47.000 --> 26:49.800
You are not Yu Jeong Rin.

26:53.033 --> 26:55.153
Do you remember

26:55.153 --> 26:57.700
Jeong Rin?

26:57.700 --> 26:59.300
Yes.

27:07.167 --> 27:10.000
Hey, why are you crying?

27:11.200 --> 27:12.800
Are you okay?

27:15.034 --> 27:16.567
[Map]

27:16.567 --> 27:18.667
It should be around here,

27:18.667 --> 27:19.900
where Ms. Park met him.

27:19.900 --> 27:22.667
It was a month
before Yu Jeong Rin was murdered.

27:22.667 --> 27:26.567
Like you said, he's truly
obsessed with stockings.

27:26.567 --> 27:28.567
He's a complete psycho.

27:36.533 --> 27:38.733
He hides in places like this.

27:52.167 --> 27:55.968
He waits and waits

27:55.968 --> 27:58.000
for the right target.

28:11.800 --> 28:14.000
Then he makes his move.

28:16.767 --> 28:21.067
If he gets spotted,
he plays dead like a scarecrow.

28:26.200 --> 28:28.233
And when the distance closes,

28:29.333 --> 28:30.967
he attacks.

28:33.567 --> 28:35.933
We'll never catch him with patrols alone.

28:35.933 --> 28:37.800
Then...

28:37.800 --> 28:39.467
We make him come to us on his own.

28:39.467 --> 28:41.633
Get everyone
to the conference room. Right now!

28:41.633 --> 28:43.233
Yes, sir.

28:49.667 --> 28:51.700
How could that happen?

28:51.700 --> 28:53.504
Jeong Rin

28:53.504 --> 28:57.033
always kept her promises.

28:57.033 --> 29:01.267
She must've wanted to keep her promise to you

29:01.267 --> 29:03.600
about coming to buy the reference books.

29:04.500 --> 29:06.528
Jeong Rin

29:06.528 --> 29:08.033
had such a good friend.

29:10.000 --> 29:11.900
Mister.

29:11.900 --> 29:13.500
Yeah?

29:15.367 --> 29:18.767
Could you at least remember Jeong Rin's name?

29:21.167 --> 29:22.800
Me?

29:24.233 --> 29:27.000
Jeong Rin would've liked that.

29:31.333 --> 29:33.033
Alright.

29:36.667 --> 29:38.200
Want more?

29:38.200 --> 29:39.833
Yes, please.

29:44.800 --> 29:46.733
That's...

29:48.832 --> 29:50.133
[Please claim your lost items]

29:50.133 --> 29:52.410
Someone must've left it,
but no one's come for it.

29:55.167 --> 29:59.000
Is there any ID inside? Or a wallet?

29:59.000 --> 30:00.500
I haven't opened it.

30:00.500 --> 30:02.933
It's someone else's purse,
so rummaging through it feels wrong.

30:02.933 --> 30:05.000
Well, they'll come get it, right?

30:07.967 --> 30:10.700
You must be getting busy
with the wedding prep.

30:10.700 --> 30:13.248
You've been thinking about your mother
a lot lately, haven't you?

30:13.248 --> 30:17.033
She would be so happy
if she were still alive.

30:17.033 --> 30:18.033
You think so?

30:18.033 --> 30:20.000
- Of course.
- Good work.

30:20.634 --> 30:22.433
Let's have a meal sometime.

30:22.433 --> 30:25.312
Who is that? Even the principal
came out to greet him.

30:25.312 --> 30:27.100
This way.

30:27.100 --> 30:29.067
Ms. Kang Sun Young?

30:32.233 --> 30:34.333
That's you, right?

30:34.333 --> 30:37.833
Wow, didn't expect to see you here.

30:37.833 --> 30:40.600
It's been a really long time,
hasn't it? Right?

30:41.216 --> 30:42.867
Do you know me?

30:42.867 --> 30:45.367
Of course, I do.

30:45.367 --> 30:49.200
Well, you might not remember me.

30:49.200 --> 30:51.233
It's been so long.

30:59.633 --> 31:03.367
Oh my, you must be busy,
yet you even took interest in our school.

31:03.367 --> 31:05.967
[Honesty, integrity, and diligence]
I don't know how to thank you.

31:05.967 --> 31:07.533
This is my alma mater.

31:07.533 --> 31:10.000
I'm happy to be of help.

31:10.000 --> 31:11.133
And the county head is doing well, I hope?

31:11.133 --> 31:13.967
My uncle is always busy.

31:13.967 --> 31:16.333
I'll arrange a meeting sometime soon.

31:16.333 --> 31:17.400
Sounds good.

31:17.400 --> 31:21.900
By the way, how do you know Ms. Kang?

31:21.900 --> 31:23.733
She's my friend's younger sister.

31:23.733 --> 31:25.367
Oh, I see.

31:25.367 --> 31:29.633
He's my high school buddy,
and he is a cop now.

31:29.633 --> 31:32.300
Both siblings turned out well,

31:32.300 --> 31:34.833
given their family's situation.

31:34.833 --> 31:36.833
Family situation?

31:39.833 --> 31:42.933
[Service, courtesy, and order]
Hey, everyone's here, right?

31:42.933 --> 31:44.567
Well...

31:46.467 --> 31:48.800
What are you talking about?

31:48.800 --> 31:50.900
Why should we deal with some student protest?

31:50.900 --> 31:54.167
That's not even our jurisdiction!

31:54.167 --> 31:56.767
The Olympics are next week.

31:56.767 --> 31:58.467
Jurisdiction doesn't matter now.

31:58.467 --> 32:01.633
We get deployed
based on the size of the protest.

32:01.633 --> 32:04.033
Why do you keep changing what you're saying?

32:04.033 --> 32:06.867
Weren't we supposed
to be excluded for a while?

32:06.867 --> 32:08.500
Mr. Heo, you heard that too, right?

32:08.500 --> 32:09.800
Yes, that's right.

32:09.800 --> 32:11.600
I don't know, either.

32:11.600 --> 32:13.133
They say it's the new prosecutor in charge.

32:13.133 --> 32:15.533
They're cracking down hard.
What am I supposed to do about it?

32:15.533 --> 32:17.533
Who's the prosecutor in charge?

32:18.267 --> 32:20.544
[Protect civic order, build a bright society]
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!

32:20.544 --> 32:22.900
Military regime, step down!

32:22.900 --> 32:25.000
[Eradicate corruption]
Step down! Step down!

32:25.000 --> 32:29.200
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!
Military regime, step down!

32:29.200 --> 32:31.133
Step down! Step down!

32:31.133 --> 32:35.333
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!
Military regime, step down!

32:35.333 --> 32:37.400
[Protect civic order, build a bright society]
Step down! Step down!

32:37.400 --> 32:39.200
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!

32:39.200 --> 32:41.567
- You're back?
- Whatever.

32:41.567 --> 32:44.767
Chasing 'reds' by day

32:44.767 --> 32:47.200
and murderers by night.

32:47.200 --> 32:49.067
I'm dead tired.

32:49.067 --> 32:51.367
Would be perfect if the killer
were among them.

32:51.367 --> 32:52.800
Military regime, step down!

32:52.800 --> 32:55.567
- Let's go, back to work.
- Step down! Step down!

33:05.050 --> 33:07.073
- Forward!
- Move forward!

33:34.667 --> 33:35.667
What is this?

33:35.667 --> 33:37.333
What's going on?

33:49.946 --> 33:52.090
[Espionage, Crime, Disaster,
Reporting Center]

35:00.133 --> 35:01.733
You punk!

35:07.100 --> 35:08.800
You little...

35:09.632 --> 35:12.600
- Let go.
- Are you going to kill him?

35:12.600 --> 35:14.333
What's the big deal? He's a commie.

35:14.333 --> 35:16.133
Let go!

35:16.133 --> 35:17.433
What are you doing?

35:17.433 --> 35:18.433
What are you doing right now?

35:18.433 --> 35:20.167
Act like a proper cop!

35:20.167 --> 35:21.600
Not some thug with a badge!

35:21.600 --> 35:23.500
Are you done talking, you punk?

35:23.500 --> 35:24.967
Am I wrong?

35:24.967 --> 35:26.567
You're acting like a street punk.

35:26.567 --> 35:29.000
And what about you?
You got kicked out of Seoul!

35:29.000 --> 35:31.600
Just do what you're told, you punk!

35:31.600 --> 35:34.367
For God's sake, get a grip!

35:34.367 --> 35:38.133
Hey! Stop right there, you punk!

35:39.232 --> 35:40.333
Darn it!

35:40.333 --> 35:42.000
Hey!

35:43.900 --> 35:45.533
We have to go.

35:49.133 --> 35:50.733
This way!

36:01.800 --> 36:04.000
It's definitely Ki Beom.

36:05.067 --> 36:07.000
Why would he...

36:08.067 --> 36:09.933
Hey, you punk!

36:09.933 --> 36:12.067
I lost him because of you!

36:12.067 --> 36:13.800
Lost him?

36:15.642 --> 36:16.933
Darn it!

36:16.933 --> 36:18.533
How could you lose him?

36:18.533 --> 36:21.033
Detective Do, I told you!

36:21.033 --> 36:22.167
We can't afford to lose him.

36:22.167 --> 36:25.067
I'm sorry, sir.

36:25.067 --> 36:26.800
What are you waiting for? Go after him.

36:26.800 --> 36:28.633
Yes, sir.

36:31.133 --> 36:32.600
Was it you?

36:32.600 --> 36:35.267
The one who pulled our station officers here?

36:35.267 --> 36:36.733
Do you have any idea
what we're working on right now?

36:36.733 --> 36:40.733
This is just as serious
as the serial killings.

36:40.733 --> 36:43.467
It's a matter of national security!

36:44.733 --> 36:46.304
Don't you ever

36:46.304 --> 36:48.733
drag our detectives into this again.

36:50.533 --> 36:52.167
Detective Kang.

36:52.867 --> 36:55.167
You keep forgetting.

36:55.167 --> 36:56.933
I'm the prosecutor

36:56.933 --> 36:59.067
before I'm your friend.

36:59.802 --> 37:02.016
- You!
- Wait!

37:21.067 --> 37:23.808
I'm really annoyed too

37:23.808 --> 37:25.767
in this situation.

37:32.762 --> 37:37.370
[Kangseng Bookstore]

37:44.333 --> 37:45.967
Tae Joo!

37:49.067 --> 37:51.100
Why did you go there?

37:51.100 --> 37:52.900
Why did I go where?

38:02.900 --> 38:05.967
So I'm supposed to just
watch those students get beaten?

38:05.967 --> 38:07.967
You might get hurt.

38:08.767 --> 38:11.433
If I see you at a place like that again,

38:11.433 --> 38:14.033
I'll lock you up then.

38:14.033 --> 38:15.833
Remember that.

38:29.267 --> 38:31.300
A sting operation?

38:31.300 --> 38:33.033
[Investigation Team 2]
Yes.

38:33.033 --> 38:34.967
The plan is simple.

38:35.833 --> 38:38.300
We draw the suspect out
from wherever he's hiding

38:39.600 --> 38:41.733
onto the street.

38:43.833 --> 38:47.300
So you're suggesting
a female officer as bait.

38:47.300 --> 38:50.500
- Yes, exactly.
- But how do we know where he'll show up?

38:52.667 --> 38:56.100
As you know, he's got weapon.

38:56.100 --> 38:59.533
No one knows what might happen
during the operation.

38:59.533 --> 39:02.400
Anyone who doesn't want in can step out.

39:10.867 --> 39:14.567
Sir, we're police too.

39:14.567 --> 39:17.767
We really want to catch the suspect.

39:17.767 --> 39:19.400
Me too!

39:31.667 --> 39:34.233
One woman and two men.

39:34.233 --> 39:37.067
Each team will consist of
at least three people.

39:48.367 --> 39:52.400
The suspect has a habit of
disguising himself as a scarecrow.

39:53.533 --> 39:55.683
If you see a scarecrow,

39:55.683 --> 39:57.600
be sure to check it.

40:37.233 --> 40:39.067
Good work.

40:42.400 --> 40:44.200
Miss!

40:44.200 --> 40:47.733
- Oh, Hye Jin!
- Kook Hee was taken away in an ambulance!

40:47.733 --> 40:50.367
She was hit by a motorcycle
in front of the school.

40:50.367 --> 40:53.500
- Which hospital?
- Probably Jeil Hospital nearby.

40:53.500 --> 40:54.533
Let's take my car.

40:54.533 --> 40:56.233
- Okay.
- Come here.

40:56.233 --> 40:58.970
Let's go home. My goodness.

40:58.970 --> 41:03.130
Hey, come with me!

41:03.130 --> 41:05.045
Let's go!

41:14.500 --> 41:16.100
Sun Young...

41:25.367 --> 41:27.136
Thank goodness,

41:27.136 --> 41:29.133
it didn't get any worse.

41:29.133 --> 41:30.167
It's a relief.

41:30.167 --> 41:32.600
She'll be discharged soon.

41:32.600 --> 41:34.700
I'll drive you back.

41:34.700 --> 41:35.933
It's okay. No need.

41:35.933 --> 41:38.867
Come on. We're going the same way anyway.

41:39.900 --> 41:41.533
Well, then...

41:53.100 --> 41:55.167
[Closed]

41:58.933 --> 42:01.733
Why does he keep blowing up the phone?

42:01.733 --> 42:06.133
He said Sun Young got into
some guy's car and went away.

42:06.133 --> 42:07.133
What?

42:07.133 --> 42:08.133
What kind of car?

42:08.133 --> 42:10.333
A Grandeur.

42:10.333 --> 42:12.567
Pretty nice.

42:12.567 --> 42:15.667
Sun Young isn't the type to go for money.

42:15.667 --> 42:18.300
She cares about looks.

42:18.300 --> 42:21.200
Oh, come on.

42:21.200 --> 42:24.433
My mother always says
beauty doesn't last a few years anyway.

42:24.433 --> 42:26.833
You can't live off looks.

42:28.567 --> 42:30.567
There must be a reason.

42:32.300 --> 42:34.267
Don't you trust Sun Young?

42:34.967 --> 42:36.600
That's not it.

42:38.400 --> 42:40.000
Hey,

42:40.000 --> 42:41.900
who took this out?

42:42.967 --> 42:44.300
What's that drawing?

42:44.300 --> 42:46.833
Don't touch other people's things!

42:46.833 --> 42:48.967
A customer left it behind.

43:02.867 --> 43:06.500
[Kangseng Police Station]

43:08.767 --> 43:11.400
Ms. Lee, you're off today's operation.

43:11.400 --> 43:14.433
No, it's okay. I can do it.

43:14.433 --> 43:15.552
You can't even walk properly,

43:15.552 --> 43:17.533
- so how would you do it?
- But...

43:17.533 --> 43:18.967
Just stay.

43:18.967 --> 43:20.600
I can do it.

43:20.600 --> 43:22.200
Have a seat.

43:26.067 --> 43:28.567
Then what about our team today?

43:28.567 --> 43:30.200
Mr. Park.

43:30.867 --> 43:32.933
Want to try wearing a skirt?

43:34.167 --> 43:35.967
It might suit you.

43:35.967 --> 43:37.767
That's a bit...

43:40.700 --> 43:42.300
Hey!

43:43.600 --> 43:44.733
Got a substitute.

43:44.733 --> 43:46.367
A substitute?

43:47.433 --> 43:49.067
I'll do it.

43:49.933 --> 43:51.367
I did good, right?

43:51.367 --> 43:54.000
Mr. Heo, did you forget
this operation is classified?

43:54.000 --> 43:57.000
She agreed to keep it confidential.

43:57.000 --> 43:59.733
Mr. Heo, how can you trust a reporter...

43:59.733 --> 44:01.400
Ouch!

44:01.400 --> 44:04.400
You!

44:04.400 --> 44:05.733
Take me off if you want.

44:05.733 --> 44:08.967
I'll blow this wide open
in tomorrow's papers.

44:10.833 --> 44:12.967
Sorry.

44:12.967 --> 44:14.167
It's fine.

44:14.167 --> 44:16.233
Don't wear stockings.

44:18.200 --> 44:21.467
And Seo Ji Won, you listen carefully.

44:23.100 --> 44:25.500
When you're out there,

44:25.500 --> 44:30.667
if you see anything suspicious
like a scarecrow, run away immediately.

44:30.667 --> 44:32.900
Suspicious scarecrow?

44:34.167 --> 44:36.167
It might be the suspect.

44:47.500 --> 44:50.900
Wow, your place is really close to mine.

44:50.900 --> 44:53.700
From now on, ride in my car, okay?

44:53.700 --> 44:55.767
No, thank you. But I appreciate the thought.

44:55.767 --> 44:58.100
Why? The streets are scary
at night these days.

44:58.100 --> 45:00.867
My fiancé picks me up
every day, so it's fine.

45:01.633 --> 45:04.000
Oh, you are getting married?

45:04.000 --> 45:05.600
Yes.

45:05.600 --> 45:07.500
Congratulations.

45:09.300 --> 45:11.100
What kind of family is he from?

45:11.100 --> 45:13.984
Just an ordinary family.

45:14.600 --> 45:16.900
Then, does his family know

45:16.900 --> 45:19.000
about your mother?

45:22.567 --> 45:24.200
Pardon?

45:25.700 --> 45:29.467
I'm not trying to pry. It just came up.

45:29.467 --> 45:30.967
Oh dear, don't worry.

45:30.967 --> 45:33.433
I won't tell anyone about this.

45:33.433 --> 45:35.767
I'm good at keeping my mouth shut.

45:37.667 --> 45:40.467
So who do you take after, Sun Young?

45:40.467 --> 45:42.733
Your mother?

45:42.733 --> 45:44.667
Oh, right?

45:44.667 --> 45:47.333
You must have gotten your pretty face
from your mother.

45:47.333 --> 45:49.067
Let me out.

45:50.567 --> 45:52.767
Why all of a sudden?
You're making this awkward.

45:52.767 --> 45:55.200
Let me out. I'm uncomfortable.

45:55.200 --> 45:57.767
What did I even do to make you uncomfortable?

46:02.600 --> 46:04.033
Sun Young.

46:04.033 --> 46:06.667
Is that what you think of me?

46:10.567 --> 46:13.100
That's insulting.

46:13.100 --> 46:16.067
I'm not someone
who deserves to be treated like that.

46:16.067 --> 46:17.933
Do you even know
what kind of family I come from?

46:17.933 --> 46:19.167
Do you know who my uncle is?

46:19.167 --> 46:20.300
Calm down and stop the car!

46:20.300 --> 46:21.400
Who are you to give orders?

46:21.400 --> 46:23.067
You, daughter of a tramp!

46:24.067 --> 46:25.300
Stop the car now!

46:25.300 --> 46:26.367
Let go!

46:26.367 --> 46:28.100
Stop the car!

46:29.533 --> 46:31.533
Hey, let go!

47:00.122 --> 47:01.920
You wench! Get over here.

48:42.300 --> 48:45.367
Oh, it's chilly.

48:45.367 --> 48:48.400
Why did he insist on no stockings?

51:09.433 --> 51:11.267
A scarecrow...

51:11.267 --> 51:12.600
There was a scarecrow.

51:12.600 --> 51:17.033
And I think I heard stray dogs too.

51:17.033 --> 51:19.033
Stray dogs.

51:19.033 --> 51:20.633
No way.

51:25.967 --> 51:27.400
When you're out there,

51:27.400 --> 51:31.000
if you see anything suspicious
like a scarecrow, run away immediately.

51:31.000 --> 51:32.767
Suspicious scarecrow?

51:32.767 --> 51:34.733
It might be the suspect.

52:25.633 --> 52:26.833
Police.

52:26.833 --> 52:28.100
It's okay. Calm down.

52:28.100 --> 52:29.600
Police, police.

52:29.600 --> 52:31.300
I'm police.

52:34.567 --> 52:37.500
It's okay now, it's okay.

52:37.500 --> 52:39.200
You're safe now.

52:40.700 --> 52:42.600
Where did that punk go?

52:46.000 --> 52:47.000
Where is he?

52:47.000 --> 52:48.367
Why are you here?

52:48.367 --> 52:49.833
- Where is Ji Won?
- She's not here?

52:49.833 --> 52:52.100
That's him!

52:53.767 --> 52:55.567
Mr. Park, look after her
and go to the car first.

52:55.567 --> 52:56.567
Report our location.

52:56.567 --> 52:58.167
Yes, sir.

53:50.867 --> 53:52.500
Ji Won!

53:53.267 --> 53:54.900
Seo Ji Won!

53:57.300 --> 54:00.467
Seo Ji Won! Answer me!

54:00.467 --> 54:02.100
Seo Ji Won!

54:11.933 --> 54:14.000
Ji Won!

54:14.000 --> 54:16.200
Ji Won!

54:16.200 --> 54:17.967
Ji Won, wake up!

54:17.967 --> 54:19.067
Seo Ji Won!

54:19.067 --> 54:20.333
Ji Won!

54:20.333 --> 54:21.900
Hey, stay with me!

54:21.900 --> 54:25.000
Hey, Ji Won. Seo Ji Won!

54:30.100 --> 54:31.733
Ji Won!

54:57.667 --> 55:01.367
The surgery went well,
but whether there's brain damage is still...

55:17.300 --> 55:18.900
Tae Joo.

55:19.600 --> 55:22.767
I'll stay here, so you should...

55:23.867 --> 55:25.733
I think you should go.

55:25.733 --> 55:28.300
Where should I go?

55:29.100 --> 55:31.200
Hey.

55:31.200 --> 55:32.800
Your sister

55:34.233 --> 55:36.067
is in this hospital.

55:40.300 --> 55:41.933
Sun Young...

55:49.658 --> 55:51.898
[Kang Sun Young]

56:01.000 --> 56:02.633
Sun Young!

56:06.033 --> 56:07.867
What on earth...

56:14.467 --> 56:16.467
Still no word?

56:17.933 --> 56:21.500
Wait, have you checked everywhere
he might've gone?

56:25.033 --> 56:27.167
That's...

56:27.167 --> 56:28.767
Sir.

56:30.267 --> 56:31.400
Do you have time?

56:31.400 --> 56:34.567
Yeah, I'll call you later.

56:35.367 --> 56:36.633
I have something important to tell you...

56:36.633 --> 56:38.200
Oh, come on!

56:38.200 --> 56:41.400
What on earth could be so urgent
for you to make this big a fuss over?

56:44.533 --> 56:46.167
Sir.

56:46.933 --> 56:48.800
It will only take a moment.

57:32.000 --> 57:33.467
Hey, you punk!

57:33.467 --> 57:35.840
Relax, relax!

57:35.840 --> 57:36.967
Listen.

57:36.967 --> 57:38.733
Hey, lift your head.

57:38.733 --> 57:40.933
Relax!

57:40.933 --> 57:42.633
You punk!

57:42.633 --> 57:44.267
Hyeon Cheol!

57:46.300 --> 57:47.467
Hyeon Cheol!

57:47.467 --> 57:49.667
Hyeon Cheol, stay with me!

57:49.667 --> 57:51.300
Hyeon Cheol!

57:52.233 --> 57:53.433
Dad...

57:53.433 --> 57:55.072
Yeah,

57:55.072 --> 57:56.700
I'm here.

57:56.700 --> 58:00.200
What on earth happened here?

58:00.200 --> 58:03.400
I told you to make some time for me, sir.

58:05.933 --> 58:07.967
Was it you?

58:07.967 --> 58:09.633
You're the one who did this to my son?

58:09.633 --> 58:12.933
Sir, it's not about Hyeon Cheol
getting hit a few times.

58:14.567 --> 58:16.467
Did you know

58:16.467 --> 58:21.567
your son committed a serious violation
of the National Security Law?

58:22.433 --> 58:24.333
What?

58:24.333 --> 58:26.733
If you knew and turned a blind eye,

58:27.467 --> 58:30.333
this won't be something
we can contain within the prosecution.

58:31.467 --> 58:33.100
You punk!

58:40.933 --> 58:43.200
Is it true the serial killer showed up today?

58:43.200 --> 58:44.767
Has he been caught yet?

58:44.767 --> 58:46.533
Let's leave before this gets any louder.

58:46.533 --> 58:48.333
Jeez, how did things end up like this?

58:48.333 --> 58:50.700
So she's the daughter of a bar madam.

58:50.700 --> 58:52.967
I'm quite shocked as well.

59:00.954 --> 59:02.457
- Hey!
- Stop!

59:04.730 --> 59:06.333
- Stop it!
- What's going on?

59:06.333 --> 59:09.167
Hey, what are you doing?
Hold back the reporters!

59:09.167 --> 59:11.233
Block them!

59:12.667 --> 59:15.100
Someone help!

59:15.100 --> 59:16.600
- Hey, you punk!
- Stop it!

59:16.600 --> 59:20.384
[Police officer arrested
for assaulting an active teacher]

59:21.967 --> 59:23.767
What are you going to do about this?

59:24.433 --> 59:27.133
Why are you targeting innocent people
instead of the real criminal?

59:27.133 --> 59:28.700
He's not exactly innocent.

59:28.700 --> 59:29.767
What?

59:29.767 --> 59:31.567
But arresting Detective Kang?

59:31.567 --> 59:34.200
How can you arrest someone
before an investigation?

59:34.200 --> 59:36.100
Why not? He got caught red-handed.

59:36.100 --> 59:39.933
After what happened to his sister,
what kind of brother wouldn't lose it?

59:39.933 --> 59:42.133
So what, a police officer
can just beat a civilian?

59:42.133 --> 59:44.067
And even in front of reporters?

59:49.267 --> 59:55.133
The prosecutor in charge already
issued the arrest warrant, so what can we do?

01:00:02.233 --> 01:00:04.067
- Officer Jeong.
- Yes.

01:00:04.067 --> 01:00:06.400
Let me use the phone, quickly.

01:00:06.400 --> 01:00:07.967
Come on, quickly.

01:00:07.967 --> 01:00:09.067
No, you can't.

01:00:09.067 --> 01:00:10.400
Bring it now!

01:00:10.400 --> 01:00:11.900
Bring it, come here, Ji Hwan.

01:00:11.900 --> 01:00:13.000
Hurry up.

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:14.367
I really can't.

01:00:14.367 --> 01:00:16.067
It's fine.

01:00:16.067 --> 01:00:17.667
Bring it here. Darn it.

01:00:20.567 --> 01:00:22.200
I'll be quick.

01:00:24.600 --> 01:00:27.967
This is a total mess.

01:00:27.967 --> 01:00:29.600
Hey, bring it here!

01:00:30.233 --> 01:00:31.833
Put the phone down.

01:00:31.833 --> 01:00:33.533
I'll be quick.

01:00:33.533 --> 01:00:35.133
Sorry, Mr. Kang.

01:00:45.233 --> 01:00:46.900
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

01:00:46.900 --> 01:00:49.600
There's a critical patient.

01:00:49.600 --> 01:00:51.867
I just need to check the patient's condition.

01:00:52.567 --> 01:00:55.800
Calling won't wake her up.

01:00:57.500 --> 01:00:59.767
Go get questioned.

01:00:59.767 --> 01:01:00.767
On what?

01:01:00.767 --> 01:01:04.600
The assault on Jeon Kyeong Ho.
That's my jurisdiction.

01:01:07.967 --> 01:01:09.333
Jeez.

01:01:09.333 --> 01:01:12.200
Are you seriously
going to lock me up over that?

01:01:12.200 --> 01:01:15.933
You think the case is going
to be handed to you now?

01:01:17.600 --> 01:01:19.833
It's already mine.

01:01:19.833 --> 01:01:21.267
What?

01:01:21.267 --> 01:01:23.100
I told you.

01:01:23.100 --> 01:01:25.500
I'd take it back.

01:01:25.500 --> 01:01:28.300
You, and the case.

01:01:53.500 --> 01:01:55.233
He still hasn't come?

01:01:57.133 --> 01:02:00.333
Well, he's exercising.

01:02:00.333 --> 01:02:01.367
Exercising?

01:02:01.367 --> 01:02:05.933
Yes, inmate 1045
has a morning exercise routine.

01:02:05.933 --> 01:02:09.800
He'll be done soon, so please wait a little.

01:02:10.833 --> 01:02:13.167
Lee Yong Woo is sure diligent.

01:02:14.233 --> 01:02:15.833
He's like that about everything.

01:02:15.833 --> 01:02:19.133
Health, woodworking, all of it.

01:02:21.867 --> 01:02:23.467
I see.

01:02:27.767 --> 01:02:30.433
Oh dear, I'm a little late...

01:02:31.167 --> 01:02:32.233
Where did he go?

01:02:32.233 --> 01:02:34.167
- Gone.
- Gone?

01:02:34.167 --> 01:02:36.900
Yes, he said he'd come tomorrow afternoon.

01:02:36.900 --> 01:02:38.967
So it doesn't interfere
with your workout routine.

01:02:47.500 --> 01:02:49.633
Let's go, officer.

01:03:28.467 --> 01:03:30.767
Detective Kang Tae Joo is being removed
from all investigations, effective today.

01:03:30.767 --> 01:03:33.200
Let's just take his resignation
quietly and end it.

01:03:33.200 --> 01:03:34.200
Don't worry.

01:03:34.200 --> 01:03:36.833
I don't care about means or methods, either.

01:03:36.833 --> 01:03:38.733
Do you really have to quit being a cop?

01:03:38.733 --> 01:03:41.000
[Kangseng Bookstore]
Just catch him for me, sir.

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:42.733
Any last words?

01:03:42.733 --> 01:03:44.333
Make sure to catch that punk

01:03:44.333 --> 01:03:46.300
before he kills anyone else.

01:03:48.400 --> 01:03:49.400
Sir!

01:03:49.400 --> 01:03:51.133
Well, the body... It's another murder.

01:03:51.133 --> 01:03:52.733
We found it!
